Package: modbus-proxy-manager
Version: 0.1.0
Section: net
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: Xerolux <xerolux@github.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/Xerolux/modbridge
Description: Modern Modbus TCP Proxy Manager with Web Interface
 ModBridge is a modern, robust Modbus TCP proxy manager with an elegant
 web interface. It enables the management of multiple Modbus TCP proxy
 instances through a central web interface.
 .
 Key Features:
  - Multi-proxy support: Manage multiple Modbus TCP proxy instances
  - Web interface: Modern, responsive UI (embedded in binary)
  - Real-time monitoring: Live traffic logging via Server-Sent Events
  - Security: Admin authentication with bcrypt hashing
  - Persistence: JSON-based configuration with export/import
  - Single binary: Entire frontend embedded in Go binary
  - Graceful shutdown: Clean shutdown of all proxy instances
  - Health checks: Integrated health checks for container environments
 .
 Performance:
  - Latency (avg): ~3-5ms
  - Throughput: ~10,000 req/s
  - Memory (idle): ~8MB
Depends: systemd, adduser
